  "text": "r immutable data chunks that compactly store genomic data and metadata in the distributed filesystem. Figure 1 gives an overview of our database. We implemented our own indices and ancillary data structures to optimize all operations, and bypass the Hadoop NameNode whenever possible to reduce the end-to-end latency of the queries. We do not rely on higher-level Hadoop data structures such as those offered by SpatialHadoop [CITATION_1] or Impala (http://www.cloudera.com/content/ cloudera/en/products-and-services/cdh/impala.html), since these higher-level structures negatively impact the performance of on-line queries. Along similar lines, we do not directly use large-scale batch-processing features a la MapReduce, since they would introduce unreasonably high latencies in our context, but could take advantage of such functionalities for off-line operations such as batch updates or complex analytics.",
